repo.name: cython

body:
I can see that some users still get confused and I think we can improve wording and some templates to be nicer to handle, so people could understand we what from them more easily and be less overwhelmed 

What I've changed:

- Removed blank issue and renamed "other" to be blank issue template with text
- Updated some titles, descriptions
- Separated environment section into `input` fields and made it so `[e.g. X]` are not there, but are just suggestions
- Renamed issue templates so it would be possible to sort them in any order we want (`name.yml` -> `{id}_name.yml`, github uses alphabetical ordering)

I temporarily made it a default branch so you can try those templates with [my fork](https://github.com/0dminnimda/cython/issues/new/choose)
Bug report will look like [this](https://github.com/0dminnimda/cython/issues/5#issue-1551318569)
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/52697657/213785201-b46d820c-3abe-4304-a523-10a64c5b751a.png)

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/52697657/213778719-c8c65371-3b18-453a-b001-d33562e128db.png)
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/52697657/213778881-c496adde-2641-4584-baa1-0635150e3f5a.png)

> **Note** I don't think this vulnerability issue is gonna be in the cython repo, I tried to get rid of it, it stayed no matter what

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/52697657/213778758-5c4cbb2f-5341-43bc-95f4-bdb12417e334.png)
